Package com.github.cdefgah.bencoder4j.model

Class BencodedDictionary

java.lang.Object
com.github.cdefgah.bencoder4j.model.BencodedObject
com.github.cdefgah.bencoder4j.model.BencodedDictionary
public final class BencodedDictionary
extends BencodedObject
Represents bencoded dictionary object.
See Also:
Bencode reference

Please note that this implementation is not synchronized. If multiple threads access a BencodedDictionary instance concurrently, and at least one of the threads modifies the object structurally, it must be synchronized externally.

    • containsValue

      public boolean containsValue​(BencodedObject value)
      Returns true if this map maps one or more keys to the specified value. More formally, returns true if and only if this map contains at least one mapping to a value v such that (value==null ? v==null : value.equals(v)).

      This operation will probably require time linear in the map size for most implementations.

      Parameters:
      value - value whose presence in this map is to be tested.
      Returns:
      true if a mapping to value exists; false otherwise.
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if value is null.
